# 4. ひとりでも

Akito: ...?!
Akito: (What just happened? Everything went blurry all of a sudden...)
Staff Member: “Hey, Akito, you okay? You're on soon.”
Akito: (He's speaking English...?)
Akito: (Wait, of course he is... I'm in the US.)
Akito: “Sorry, I'm just a bit light-headed.”
Staff Member: “Whoa, don't go collapsing on stage or anything, okay?”
Akito: “I'm fine. And this crowd won't know what hit them.”
Akito: ♪———————! ——————!
Akito: (That's right. On your feet...!)
Audience: “Hey, is he from Japan...?”
Audience: “Seems like it. He's really young, but he sounds pretty good.”
Audience: “You're doing great, Akito!!!”
Akito: (No, I can still do better. A lot better...!)
Akito: ♪——————————!
Akito: (I need to be more...!)
Akito: Phew...
Staff Member: “You had them bouncing off the walls, Akito!”
Akito: “Haha. Thanks.”
Akito: (Yeah, the crowd reacted pretty well... I still remember the crickets I heard when I first came over here.)
Akito: (In that sense, things have gotten a lot better...)
Akito: (But this still isn't enough to surpass RAD WEEKEND.)
Akito: (I need to learn how to get the crowd going even more and improve my technique...!)
Staff Member: “Hm? You're leaving already, Akito?”
Akito: “Yeah, I still need to finish my training routine for today.”
Staff Member: “You're so diligent. But why not hang out with some other musicians for a change?”
Staff Member: “Sam and the others were just looking for you. They wanted to see if you'd be interested in going to the after-party.”
Akito: (Actually, I might learn something new by talking to other musicians.)
Akito: “Okay, I'll go.”
Musicians: “There you are, Akito!”
Akito: “Hey.”
Musicians: “You put on another great performance today.”
Akito: “I appreciate you saying that, but I still have a lot of work left to do.”
Akito: “I mean, what's the point if I can't get everyone in the place fired up?”
Musicians: “Haha. You don't sound satisfied at all. I like that hungry spirit of yours!”
Musicians: “I really admire your work ethic. I still remember when you could barely get two words out in English...”
Akito: “That doesn't matter now since I'm a way better speaker now...”
Musicians: “Haha. True!”
Musicians: “Still, Akito, you've grown so much in a lot of different respects.”
Musicians: “I agree. Every time we watch you perform, we're stunned by how much you've grown since the last time.”
Musicians: “So, Akito, how would you feel about teaming up with us?”
Akito: “Thank you, but I can't.”
Musicians: “Whoa, that was fast! You won't even try it out for a little bit?”
Musicians: “You aren't helping things by being so overbearing.”
Akito: “No, it's nothing like that.”
Akito: “I've already decided that I'm not going to team up with anyone.”
Musicians: “Wait, why? Did something happen?”
Akito: “No...”
Akito: Vivids broke up...?
Toya: Yes, that's right.
Akito: ...
Akito: Dammit...!
Akito: If they couldn't make it through that, then that means they've reached their ceiling.
Akito: If they're not committed like we are, they're never going to surpass RAD WEEKEND. Right?
Akito: We have to forget about them and keep moving forward, Toya.
Toya: ...
Akito: Toya...?
Toya: Akito...
Toya: Let's stop all this.
Akito: Huh? What are you talking about?
Toya: I...
Toya: I can't keep going after this childish dream.
Akito: ...!
Akito: (At first, I thought his dad was behind what he said.)
Akito: (But he was adamant about quitting.)
Akito: (And by the time I calmed down and felt ready to talk to him, he'd left Japan.)
Akito: (If only I'd contacted him sooner...)
Akito: (No, what's done is done. There's no use thinking about this any further...)
Akito: (I just have to keep singing. Alone.)
Akito: (Because... I think that's the best way for me to rise to the top.)
Musicians: “While we're on the subject...”
Musicians: “Why did you decide to start singing over here, Akito? Are you chasing after a particular artist or something?”
Akito: “There's an event that I want to surpass...”
Musicians: “Surpass?”
Akito: “Yes. An event that I'm willing to spend my entire life on trying to surpass.”
Akito: “Which is why, I...”
Akito: “I'm focused on doing just that right now.”
Musicians: “Cool! That's awesome.”
???: <...pen...eyes...>
Akito: (What was that just now...?)
Musicians: “What's wrong, Akito?”
Akito: “Oh, it's nothing...”
Akito: (Did I imagine that...?)
Akito: (I thought I heard someone else's voice just now.)
Akito: Hm? A message? From who...?
Akito: ...!
